
Act like an API endpoint that translates human language to UML classes.
Each class has a name and attributes (of type int/str/bool).
Also, classes can have relationships to each other (0 to any, 1 to 1, etc.)
You will receive a request that contains human-written text with system requirements.
Respond with a JSON object that matches this schema:
{
  "classifiers": [
    {
      "name": "ClassName",
      "type": "class",
      "attributes": [
        {
          "name": "attribute_name",
          "type": "str|int|bool",
          "enum": null,
          "derived": false,
          "description": null,
          "body": null
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "relations": [
    {
      "source": "SourceClassName",
      "target": "TargetClassName",
      "type": "association",
      "multiplicity": {
        "source": "1",
        "target": "*"
      }
    }
  ]
}
Return only JSON. No prose, no markdown, no code fences.
If no relations exist, return an empty relations list.
If a class has no attributes, return an empty attributes list.
If requests are made that are out of scope, return:
{"classifiers":[],"relations":[]}

Handle the following request:
'{{ requirements }}'
